^-{ ^*BDeal of the Week 343 - April 7, 2003^*N
 ^*BBy Fred Gitelman^*N }
^-
Norway's ^*BGeir Helgemo^*N is widely considered to be one of the world's best players and his brilliant exploits as declarer have appeared several times over the years in this feature. This week's deal is another Helgemo masterpiece. Geir was playing in a practice match with ^*BJimmy Cayne^*N (who has been winning major ACBL events for over 30 years) when this week's deal was played.

I would like to thank my friend ^*BGeo Tislevoll^*N for bringing this deal to my attention. Geo is another one of Norway's top players and he is also a gifted writer who has taken a special interest in Geir Helgemo's remarkable bridge talents. Geo is the author of the book, ^*IHelgemo's World of Bridge^*N.

This book contains dozens of beautiful deals that Geir was involved in, but it also contains Geo's personal observations about Geir himself. Geo and Geir began their friendship when Geir was only 12 years old and just starting out as a bridge player. For the past 20 years Geo has watched Geir grow into the champion and man that he has become today. In ^*IHelgemo's World of Bridge^*N Geo is thus able to offer a unique perspective on the talents and character of one of the greatest bridge players of our time.

I am confident that regular readers of ^*BThe Deal of the Week^*N will enjoy reading ^*IHelgemo's World of Bridge^*N (published by ^*BFive Aces Books^*N and available through major bridge supply houses).

If Geo ever writes a sequel to ^*IHelgemo's World of Bridge^*N, you can bet that this week's deal will be included in it (you can also bet that I will buy such a book)!


