The original ^*ILearn to Play Bridge^*N program was released in 1999 and it was also offered for free through the ACBL's web site. Over 250,000 people have downloaded this program and I have received a great deal of positive feedback from people who have used this program to either learn to play bridge or to brush up on their skills.

While both of these programs are available as free downloads, their development was quite expensive. Both programs contain the equivalent of about 500 pages of material and I spent 6 months of (very) full time work developing each of these programs. I am grateful to the ACBL and the ^*BACBL Education Foundation^*N for financing these projects in the hope of increasing the number of bridge players out there. My special thanks goes out to ^*BJulie Greenberg^*N and ^*BBetty Starzec^*N of the ACBL's Educational Department for the help and support they gave me while I worked on these programs.

The ACBL receives a lot of criticism these days, but they deserve nothing but praise for their involvement in this project. If you have a friend who wants to learn to play bridge or is an intermediate player who is eager to improve, please tell him or her about ^*ILearn to Play Bridge^*N and ^*ILearn to Play Bridge 2^*N!

